#  $Id: link_rules,v 1.1.8.1 2006/08/16 20:09:13 theurich Exp $
#
#  link_rules
#

The following commands show how to link a Fortran90 application with the ESMF 
shared libraries on Compaq. In the command, the Fortran90 application is 
called "myModel".

It is assumed that the ESMF libraries have been built successfully at ESMF_DIR 
with the following environment variables:
ESMF_OS = OSF1
ESMF_COMPILER = default
ESMF_ABI = 64
ESMF_SITE = default
ESMF_COMM = mpi
ESMF_BOPT = g or O

To simplify the link rules, first define MODDIR and LIBDIR.

MODDIR = ${ESMF_DIR}/mod/mod${ESMF_BOPT}/OSF1.default.64.default
LIBDIR = ${ESMF_DIR}/lib/lib${ESMF_BOPT}/OSF1.default.64.default

The link rules are:

f90 -free -I${MODDIR} myModel.F  -L${LIBDIR} -rpath ${LIBDIR}  -lesmf  -lcxx -lmpi -o myModel
